Name: non-invasive bladder papillary urothelial neoplasm
Definition: An ovarian germ cell teratoma that is composed of tissues that originate from two or three of the following germ layers
Synonym: Papillary urothelial neoplasm of low malignant potential

Name: bladder transitional cell papilloma
Definition: A benign perivascular tumor that is characterized as a vascular variant of a glomus tumor.
